        <title>4 Essential Markdown Tools</title>
        <link>https://mansoorbarri.com/essential-markdown-tools/</link>
        <pubDate>Mon, 03 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mansoorbarri.com/essential-markdown-tools/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;I started using Markdown since I have been using Hugo (2020). It is pretty easy to pick up and nothing more to it however some tools make it easier to edit Markdown and some are just good to
have as a utility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are four of these tools:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://euangoddard.github.io/clipboard2markdown/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;clipboard2markdown&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://www.digitalocean.com/community/markdown&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Markdown Editor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://github.com/hackmdio/codimd&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;codimd&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://md2pdf.netlify.app/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;md2pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;clipboard2markdown&#34;&gt;clipboard2markdown&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just a simple website which turns anything into Markdown. This is particularly useful when you have a normal formatted text (I.e., from Word) and you want it in Markdown.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://mansoorbarri.com/img/guides/2024/essential-markdown-tools/clipboard2markdown.png&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;A screenshot of clipboard2markdown&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;markdown-editor&#34;&gt;Markdown Editor&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This tool is useful when you want to edit on a public computer. A saver for me as I do most of my work from college.
&lt;img src=&#34;https://mansoorbarri.com/img/guides/2024/essential-markdown-tools/markdown-editor.png&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;A screenshot of the markdown editor&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;codimd&#34;&gt;codimd&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have actually never used this one however it can be useful if you collaborate with multiple people in a Markdown project.
&lt;img src=&#34;https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hackmdio/codimd/develop/public/screenshot.png&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;A screenshot of codimd&#34;
	
	
&gt;
&lt;em&gt;image from codimd&amp;rsquo;s Github&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;md2pdf&#34;&gt;md2pdf&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have used this many times and it is quite useful when you want to send markdown files to someone. A simple markdown to pdf converter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://media.giphy.com/media/MuAtuqUGnn2PKsXhs6/giphy.gif&#34;
	
	
	
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;A GIF of md2pdf working&#34;
	
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;GIF from md2pdf&amp;rsquo;s GitHub&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s it, let me know if there are other Markdown tools you use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-MB&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
        </item>
        <item>
        <title>How to install Neovim on Debian the right way</title>
        <link>https://mansoorbarri.com/neovim-debian/</link>
        <pubDate>Sun, 14 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://mansoorbarri.com/neovim-debian/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Installing &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://neovim.io&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;Neovim&lt;/a&gt; can be confusing as it is available on most distributions and on Snap store as well however, all those packages are quite old and will not work with various vim plugins like Lazyvim.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Same goes for Debian, which I am using while learning Vim. This is the only way which works as of now an is quite easy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-curl&#34;&gt;Install Curl&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need &lt;code&gt;wget&lt;/code&gt; for this. It is installed on all system but if you don&amp;rsquo;t have it, you can install it using:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo apt install wget 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;download-neovim-app-image&#34;&gt;Download Neovim App Image&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here we will use &lt;code&gt;wget&lt;/code&gt; to pull Neovim&amp;rsquo;s app image:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;wget https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/latest/download/nvim.appimage
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;once done, make the app image executable:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;chmod +x ./nvim.appimage 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now move the app image binary to &lt;code&gt;/usr/local/bin&lt;/code&gt; so you can run it from &lt;code&gt;$PATH&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo mv nvim.appimage /usr/local/bin/nvim
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;now you can run neovim with &lt;code&gt;nvim&lt;/code&gt; command and install plugins normally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;uninstalling&#34;&gt;Uninstalling&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;when you want to uninstall Neovim, just run this command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo rm -R /usr/local/bin/nvim
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Happy coding!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-MB&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
